Steps to take before using the plugin:

-OPTIONAL: to compile opxml (if needed), read the README file in org.eclipse.linuxtools.oprofile.core/opxml

-must have oprofile installed, and configured, by doing:

	yum install oprofile
	opcontrol --init

  if no vmlinux image in /boot (not vmlinuz) then must also do
	
	opcontrol --no-vmlinux

-must install the pam security wrappers by running

	./install

 in the scripts directory

-must ensure that the scripts are user-level executable by running

	./update-perms
